function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.__init__: Initializes the validation wrapper with paths to parsed simulation data and measured data. Accepts optional configuration dict for customizing validation behavior.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.validate_all: Main validation function that: 1) Discovers available simulation data, 2) Loads and parses measured data, 3) Aligns data frequencies, 4) Creates variable mappings between real and simulated data, 5) Calculates validation metrics (CVRMSE, NMBE) for each mapping, 6) Returns comprehensive results with pass/fail status.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.validate_all_vari: Validates all simulation variants against measured data. Compares base simulation and all variants, identifying which variant performs best according to validation metrics.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.discover_availabl: Scans the parsed data directory to find available simulation outputs. Identifies timeseries data, comparison files, and metadata.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.load_and_parse_re: Loads measured data from CSV files. Handles multiple formats including EnergyPlus format, wide format, and parsed format. Automatically detects and converts between formats.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.create_variable_m: Intelligently maps measured variables to simulation variables using: 1) Exact matching, 2) Fuzzy string matching, 3) Semantic understanding (e.g., 'Electricity:Facility' matches 'Facility Electricity').
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.align_frequencies: Aligns temporal frequencies between measured and simulated data. Can aggregate hourly to daily, daily to monthly, etc. based on configuration.
function_documentation.SmartValidationWrapper.align_and_validat: For a specific variable mapping, aligns the data (handling units, zones, time periods) and prepares it for metric calculation.

Validation Metrics.CVRMSE: Coefficient of Variation of Root Mean Square Error - measures relative prediction error, typically should be < 30%
Validation Metrics.NMBE: Normalized Mean Bias Error - measures systematic bias, typically should be within ±10%
Validation Metrics.MBE: Mean Bias Error - raw bias measure in original units
